1
00:01:14,720 --> 00:01:15,520
Basketball.

2
00:01:15,520 --> 00:01:17,080
You know basketball?

3
00:01:17,080 --> 00:01:18,560
Who are you looking down on?

4
00:01:18,560 --> 00:01:20,420
We can play basketball too, okay?

5
00:01:20,560 --> 00:01:21,960
You can play basketball?

6
00:01:22,080 --> 00:01:22,880
Of course.

7
00:01:25,280 --> 00:01:26,480
Hey, the ball.

8
00:01:34,160 --> 00:01:35,600
Why don't we play a game with them?

9
00:01:35,600 --> 00:01:36,280
A game?

10
00:01:37,440 --> 00:01:38,920
But we are two girls.

11
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:41,490
What are you afraid of? You have me.

12
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:46,360
Last time you finished streaming, my account gained a lot of followers.

13
00:01:46,360 --> 00:01:47,880
If you can play basketball,

14
00:01:47,880 --> 00:01:50,610
I'll record a video later, maybe it will go viral.

15
00:01:59,360 --> 00:02:00,040
Comrade,

16
00:02:00,280 --> 00:02:01,640
How about a three-on-two?

17
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:02,500
Just you three?

18
00:02:02,960 --> 00:02:04,220
Looking down on girls?

19
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:07,040
Don't underestimate us.

20
00:02:07,160 --> 00:02:09,639
I'll show you how good my boss is later.

21
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:10,759
Let's try then.

22
00:02:10,759 --> 00:02:12,080
Come on.

23
00:02:31,440 --> 00:02:32,360
Are you okay?

24
00:02:33,440 --> 00:02:34,440
I'm fine, I'm fine.

25
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:35,970
Okay, then you guys go rest.

26
00:02:40,040 --> 00:02:41,079
Boss.

27
00:02:41,079 --> 00:02:42,160
Good luck.

28
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:54,520
Oh, so early.

29
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:01,920
If everyone was as late as you,

30
00:03:01,920 --> 00:03:03,000
these supplies

31
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:05,000
would take forever to be delivered.

32
00:03:05,160 --> 00:03:06,840
I've been having an upset stomach lately.

33
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:07,560
Besides,

34
00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:08,920
being scared by you last night,

35
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:10,600
it made me feel like I lost my soul.

36
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:12,120
Ouch.

37
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:14,760
I think you miss your little sweetheart,

38
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:16,560
and lost your soul over it.

39
00:03:16,560 --> 00:03:17,120
See,

40
00:03:17,440 --> 00:03:19,320
I shouldn't have told you these little secrets.

41
00:03:19,320 --> 00:03:19,920
You.

42
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:22,320
Just exercise your body when you have time.

43
00:03:24,360 --> 00:03:26,040
Don't look at me like this these past few days,

44
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:28,640
I was the captain of the school team in Nanyang.

45
00:03:28,640 --> 00:03:29,640
Oh my.

46
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:31,370
Captain of the school team?

47
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:32,160
You're bragging

48
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:33,360
to the sky.

49
00:03:33,760 --> 00:03:34,760
Don't believe me?

50
00:03:35,480 --> 00:03:36,280
I believe you.

51
00:03:36,480 --> 00:03:37,320
Of course I do.

52
00:03:38,720 --> 00:03:39,579
Then let's try.

53
00:03:40,480 --> 00:03:42,079
Okay, let's try.

54
00:03:42,440 --> 00:03:43,000
Let's go.

55
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:45,120
Let's go.

56
00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:45,800
Let's go.

57
00:04:32,840 --> 00:04:34,440
Good job, Lin Yaozu.

58
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:05,200
Lin Yaozu.

59
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:06,200
You're amazing.

60
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:07,360
So amazing.

61
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:10,640
Thank you, thank you.

62
00:05:17,440 --> 00:05:18,000
How is it?

63
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:19,000
You're amazing.

64
00:05:21,680 --> 00:05:22,760
Is your foot okay?

65
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:24,600
It's fine.

66
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:26,840
Put it down.

67
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:39,620
You know medicine too?

68
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:41,400
A little bit.

69
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:44,240
Usually we don't just drive,

70
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:46,880
we also have to learn some basic medical knowledge.

71
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:48,960
So if there are any unexpected situations,

72
00:05:48,960 --> 00:05:49,840
we can help.

73
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:54,159
I didn't expect your team to have so many skills.

74
00:05:55,280 --> 00:05:56,280
Is your head okay?

75
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:59,000
My head just got hit by your ball.

76
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:00,640
And I trusted you so much.

77
00:06:00,760 --> 00:06:02,840
You don't treat us like girls at all.

78
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:07,680
But since you mentioned it, I do recall something.

79
00:06:07,680 --> 00:06:09,600
Once, while we were transporting goods,

80
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:10,800
a truck flipped over.

81
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:13,300
Then we took the injured to the hospital.

82
00:06:13,760 --> 00:06:15,120
It wasn't until we got to the hospital

83
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:16,050
that we realized

84
00:06:16,360 --> 00:06:18,680
that the mechanic was actually a woman.

85
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:20,240
A woman?

86
00:06:20,960 --> 00:06:22,490
How did she hide it from you?

87
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:23,840
Could it be

88
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:25,760
that you couldn't tell the difference between a man and a woman?

89
00:06:25,760 --> 00:06:26,560
Of course not.

90
00:06:27,040 --> 00:06:28,040
Because normally,

91
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:30,200
we focused all our energy on driving.

92
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:30,960
So,

93
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:32,370
no one would notice.

94
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:35,520
We didn't know until the accident.

95
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:38,960
But didn't you

96
00:06:38,960 --> 00:06:41,240
notice anything unusual?

97
00:06:41,240 --> 00:06:43,400
Like when eating together,

98
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:45,600
sleeping,

99
00:06:45,880 --> 00:06:47,360
and showering.

100
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:50,760
We drove day and night.

101
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:52,280
We slept when we were tired,

102
00:06:52,280 --> 00:06:54,080
and kept driving when we woke up.

103
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:56,170
We didn't have regular mealtimes.

104
00:06:56,440 --> 00:06:57,560
As for showering,

105
00:06:57,560 --> 00:06:59,360
we couldn't even think about it.

106
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:02,680
Not only did we have to watch out for Japanese bombings,

107
00:07:02,680 --> 00:07:04,810
we also had to watch out for landslides

108
00:07:05,360 --> 00:07:06,440
and some

109
00:07:06,440 --> 00:07:07,500
deadly dysentery.

110
00:07:08,240 --> 00:07:09,040
Dysentery?

111
00:07:10,080 --> 00:07:10,880
Yes.

112
00:07:12,520 --> 00:07:14,640
Because some of our mechanics came back

113
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:16,440
and couldn't adjust to the food.

114
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:18,520
Plus, driving for a long time

115
00:07:18,520 --> 00:07:20,380
made them physically exhausted.

116
00:07:20,760 --> 00:07:22,960
The climate was unpredictable.

117
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:26,320
Once you got dysentery,

118
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:27,320
you basically...

119
00:07:30,080 --> 00:07:31,800
If my stomach hurts,

120
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,730
I just take some pills and I'm fine.

121
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:37,200
That's because you overeat.

122
00:07:38,840 --> 00:07:40,400
It's a good thing you live in the present.

123
00:07:40,400 --> 00:07:43,159
Otherwise, the bathroom would be your second lounge.

124
00:07:43,159 --> 00:07:44,159
Bite your tongue.

125
00:07:44,320 --> 00:07:46,240
Don't jinx it.

126
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:50,640
But, Lin Yaozu,

127
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:53,560
how many more secrets do you have?
